write interactive java program for reformatting seismic data files using java swing. use model view controller and design pattern principles. The model with be SegdBufferedFileReader or SegyBufferedFileReader class that extends BufferedFileReader as well as SEGD and SEGY writer classes. The view will be a TraceViewer class that displays X number of traces at a time. The TraceViewer will have options to apply an AGC, filter, and gain as well as display using variable density or VAWG (variable area wiggle trace). There will also be options to display headers across the top of the traces and zoom. Traces will be displayed vertically with time increasing towards the bottom. The controller will be a TraceMonitor class. The TraceMonitor class with use the model reader class to read in X number of traces at time (default is 10000). The reader objects return the traces as an array of SeismicTraces (use uploaded class). The TraceMonitor passes the SeismicTraces array to the TraceViewer. If the user is OK with what they are seeing, they can click "submit" to reformat the entire file in "batch" mode. A progress monitor should appear to show reformatting progress.
